==English==
===Etymology===
From the Arabic phrase {{ARchar|الظهر الدبّ الاكبر}} (''aƶ-ƶahr ad-dubb al-ākbar'') ‘the back of the great bear’, from {{ARchar|[[ظهر]]}} ‘back’ + {{ARchar|[[دب]]}} ‘bear’ + {{ARchar|[[اكبر]]}} ‘great’.

===Noun===
'''Dubhe'''
# [[Alpha Ursae Majoris]], a multiple [[star]] in the [[constellation]] of [[Ursa Major]], and part of the [[Plough]]

